    commented

    <a href="#issuecomment-38426371" class="timestamp">
      <time datetime="2014-03-24T09:50:22Z" is="relative-time">Mar 24, 2014</time>
    </a>
  </div>
</div>


  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p>Hm, I might have misunderstood the purpose of the v4 code. I thought it was to support fragments on old versions of Android, and that the remaining code still supports fragments on new Android devices. I could be wrong as I know nothing about fragments really. Looking at this again, I don't think that's right. </p>

<p>Lachezar is it just a question of making an impl that takes a Fragment and calls startActivityForResult on it instead? that's easy to add back if so.</p>

<p>I think people keep misunderstanding my point about open source: I do not "prefer" that people integrate by intent, though it sure seems easier for a lot of use cases. I am simply against reusing code illegally or in ways that harm the project. People keep hearing that I'm saying "don't reuse the android/ code" -- I certainly mean "you can't copy and paste the whole thing" but that is a far different statement.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

